  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 72-year-old man presents to the emergency department complaining of increasing pain, swelling, redness, and warmth at the site of a cardiac pacemaker that was implanted 3 weeks earlier. He is afebrile. The left-chest generator pocket site exhibits redness, warmth, and induration. The patient has no stigmata of infective endocarditis.\nWhat is the best next step in care for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Start empiric cefazolin"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Obtain a CT of the chest"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Aspirate the pocket site and send sample tissue for anaerobic and aerobic bacterial cultures"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Draw two sets of blood cultures"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Order a transesophageal echocardiogram"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Because of the frequency of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zb5e2996765fc68ad1a0704a5e728d062\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zb5e2996765fc68ad1a0704a5e728d062\" data-section-id=\"jRc_5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"SOay7k\">oxacillin</a> resistance among isolates that cause infection near the site of an implanted cardiac electronic device, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"GOaBFk\">vancomycin</a> is recommended as initial empiric therapy. However, treatment should only be started after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a> are obtained.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>CT of the chest may find evidence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xm0E3g&anker=Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-learningcard-id=\"xm0E3g\" data-anker=\"Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-sememe-id=\"YNan-k\">septic</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oh00Uf&anker=Zfb01fcdeb51ff26f23e3b2e25e04e156\" data-learningcard-id=\"oh00Uf\" data-anker=\"Zfb01fcdeb51ff26f23e3b2e25e04e156\" data-sememe-id=\"tk0XpT\">pulmonary emboli</a> but is not an urgent test to order and should not precede the obtaining of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-section-id=\"LZ1wX20\" data-sememe-id=\"xSaEb4\">Aspiration</a> of the pocket site can result in infection and should be avoided.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>In any patient with a possible endovascular focus of infection, it is critical to obtain at least two sets of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a> before initiating <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antimicrobial therapy</a>. Because complete removal of the device is recommended to definitively cure the infection and to prevent relapse, a specialist in electrophysiology should also be consulted.<br><br>Because of the frequency of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zb5e2996765fc68ad1a0704a5e728d062\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zb5e2996765fc68ad1a0704a5e728d062\" data-section-id=\"jRc_5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"SOay7k\">oxacillin</a> resistance among isolates that cause infection near the site of an implanted cardiac electronic device, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"GOaBFk\">vancomycin</a> is recommended as initial empiric therapy. Treatment should only be started after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a> are obtained.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> In a patient with suspected implanted cardiac-pacemaker infection and no stigmata of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Z9efab4f3e29d03e69d33b3e998efdc9f\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Z9efab4f3e29d03e69d33b3e998efdc9f\" data-sememe-id=\"Tk06MT\">infective endocarditis</a>, an essential initial step in evaluation is to draw at least two <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=p80Ln3&anker=Z07561478adc8ca51c9646960a5508186\" data-learningcard-id=\"p80Ln3\" data-anker=\"Z07561478adc8ca51c9646960a5508186\" data-section-id=\"podL1I0\" data-sememe-id=\"oi00sf\">Transesophageal echocardiography</a> may be recommended eventually for patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EH08Hh&anker=Z4bd3a5213bcec7021a2d08026fec3ee5\" data-learningcard-id=\"EH08Hh\" data-anker=\"Z4bd3a5213bcec7021a2d08026fec3ee5\" data-sememe-id=\"ER08Kf\">bacteremia</a> or those with signs of systemic infection, but it should not precede the obtaining of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a>.</div>",
