    {
      "text": "A 32-year-old woman presents with a 3-day history of fever, headache, and nausea. She had a ventriculoperitoneal shunt placed 25 years ago for congenital hydrocephalus. Temperature is 38.5°C (101.3°F), and neurological examination shows no focal deficits. CT head shows no acute changes. CSF obtained from the shunt reservoir shows a WBC count of 250/mm3 with 85% neutrophils, elevated protein, and decreased glucose. Neurosurgery has been consulted for shunt removal. What is the most appropriate empiric antibiotic therapy while awaiting culture results?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Ceftriaxone monotherapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Vancomycin and ceftazidime"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Ampicillin and gentamicin"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Clindamycin and ciprofloxacin"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Meropenem monotherapy"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zac33714c20522712f23f517fc3bbb806\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zac33714c20522712f23f517fc3bbb806\" data-section-id=\"WjcPzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"Ulabwk\">Ceftriaxone</a> alone does not provide adequate coverage against <span data-sememe-id=\"WoVPav0\">methicillin</span>-resistant variants of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=In0Yug&anker=Z1e2e48c51df99dca0da0d0a11c681fef\" data-learningcard-id=\"In0Yug\" data-anker=\"Z1e2e48c51df99dca0da0d0a11c681fef\" data-section-id=\"mYcVpa0\">gram-positive bacteria</a>, such as <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vl0GDT&anker=Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vl0GDT\" data-anker=\"Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-section-id=\"KObUtF\" data-sememe-id=\"GQYBxK\">Staphylococcus epidermidis</a>,</i> which are a common cause of shunt infections.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"GOaBFk\">Vancomycin</a> provides coverage for <span data-sememe-id=\"WoVPav0\">methicillin</span>-resistant variants of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=In0Yug&anker=Z1e2e48c51df99dca0da0d0a11c681fef\" data-learningcard-id=\"In0Yug\" data-anker=\"Z1e2e48c51df99dca0da0d0a11c681fef\" data-section-id=\"mYcVpa0\">gram-positive organisms</a>, such as <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vl0GDT&anker=Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vl0GDT\" data-anker=\"Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-section-id=\"KObUtF\" data-sememe-id=\"GQYBxK\">Staphylococcus epidermidis</a></i>, which are a common cause of shunt infections. An additional antipseudomonal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z704e6de71a61300ee265886d7485e256\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z704e6de71a61300ee265886d7485e256\" data-section-id=\"RRcl5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"-bbDwH\">beta-lactam</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6de9626e558a32ecd711aa5c2944c998\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6de9626e558a32ecd711aa5c2944c998\" data-section-id=\"WjcPzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"elaxDk\">ceftazidime</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z7dbf771bb5cba0042a1dc93dad471b17\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z7dbf771bb5cba0042a1dc93dad471b17\" data-section-id=\"WjcPzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"OJYI8J\">cefepime</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z991e430c00831fcaec1087462d3223fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z991e430c00831fcaec1087462d3223fa\" data-section-id=\"cjcazX0\" data-sememe-id=\"NOa-sk\">meropenem</a>) is recommended to cover <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=In0Yug&anker=Zca9cd6828534e5800fb9107acc256e05\" data-learningcard-id=\"In0Yug\" data-anker=\"Zca9cd6828534e5800fb9107acc256e05\" data-section-id=\"mYcVpa0\">gram-negative bacteria</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z24b906c8ffd6849b7bb44be87bf5dce9\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z24b906c8ffd6849b7bb44be87bf5dce9\" data-section-id=\"jRc_5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"iOaJHk\">Ampicillin</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-section-id=\"hjccZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"qOaCtk\">gentamicin</a> do not provide optimal coverage for the staphylococcal species that predominantly cause shunt infections. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-section-id=\"hjccZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"qOaCtk\">Gentamicin</a> has limited <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WK0P2S&anker=Zada05eaaf90f5ec68b357c7060eddf73\" data-learningcard-id=\"WK0P2S\" data-anker=\"Zada05eaaf90f5ec68b357c7060eddf73\" data-section-id=\"js1_uR0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xmb9V8\">CSF</a> penetration and is not recommended empirically for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">CNS</a> infection in adults, although it is indicated to treat <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gM0FLg&anker=Z595d8eabefda902d25f8e47e128827f5\" data-learningcard-id=\"gM0FLg\" data-anker=\"Z595d8eabefda902d25f8e47e128827f5\" data-section-id=\"iNdJaq0\" data-sememe-id=\"3z0Ssi\">neonatal meningitis</a> because it covers species that cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gM0FLg&anker=Ze801b7e117630edbbae117008afe7240\" data-learningcard-id=\"gM0FLg\" data-anker=\"Ze801b7e117630edbbae117008afe7240\" data-section-id=\"nzX7t00\" data-sememe-id=\"8p1Or30\">neonatal sepsis</a> (e.g., <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z852870e22c0e1e57e2e03e44cb249f9e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z852870e22c0e1e57e2e03e44cb249f9e\" data-section-id=\"r0cfha0\" data-sememe-id=\"BQYzyK\">Enterococcus</a></i>).</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-section-id=\"ijcJZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HOaKFk\">Clindamycin</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z3f1dbc417664139dda097bcd516ceeed\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z3f1dbc417664139dda097bcd516ceeed\" data-section-id=\"VjcGzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"flakwk\">ciprofloxacin</a> do not provide the broad-spectrum coverage needed for a suspected shunt infection. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-section-id=\"ijcJZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HOaKFk\">Clindamycin</a> has poor gram-negative coverage and poor <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">CNS</a> penetration. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z3f1dbc417664139dda097bcd516ceeed\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z3f1dbc417664139dda097bcd516ceeed\" data-section-id=\"VjcGzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"flakwk\">Ciprofloxacin</a> does provide extensive gram-negative coverage, including for <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z907d21d2f595a64844a21f931c1e50d4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z907d21d2f595a64844a21f931c1e50d4\" data-section-id=\"G0cBha0\" data-sememe-id=\"VPYGd6\">Pseudomonas</a></i>, which is important in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_f05K2&anker=Z52d549c84757de6454eb2a99eb6af0b3\" data-learningcard-id=\"_f05K2\" data-anker=\"Z52d549c84757de6454eb2a99eb6af0b3\" data-section-id=\"8J1OD30\" data-sememe-id=\"921NPT0\">health care-associated infections</a>. However, neither of these <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> provides reliable coverage for <span data-sememe-id=\"WoVPav0\">methicillin</span>-resistant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z34c8a0ce6ada8e12894a38afaa6f75c4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z34c8a0ce6ada8e12894a38afaa6f75c4\" data-section-id=\"r0cfha0\">staphylococci</a>, which commonly cause <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0s0eth&anker=Z3fe48f1a190cae1c582b40742308ca24\" data-learningcard-id=\"0s0eth\" data-anker=\"Z3fe48f1a190cae1c582b40742308ca24\" data-section-id=\"A2WR4k0\">neurosurgical device infections</a></span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z991e430c00831fcaec1087462d3223fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z991e430c00831fcaec1087462d3223fa\" data-section-id=\"cjcazX0\" data-sememe-id=\"NOa-sk\">meropenem</a> has broad-spectrum activity, monotherapy does not provide reliable coverage against <span data-sememe-id=\"WoVPav0\">methicillin</span>-resistant <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vl0GDT&anker=Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vl0GDT\" data-anker=\"Z1edd33b030fca4ea748c10bae11a7946\" data-section-id=\"KObUtF\" data-sememe-id=\"GQYBxK\">Staphylococcus epidermidis</a></i>, which is a common cause of shunt infections.</div>",
