    {
      "text": "A 63-year-old woman receiving chemotherapy for metastatic breast cancer presents to the ED with fever and rigors for two days. She denies cough, headache, abdominal pain, or dysuria. She has a right anterior chest port-a-cath for chemotherapy, which is tender to palpation, although the overlying skin appears normal. Vital signs are BP, 100/64 mm Hg; P, 118; R, 22; T, 38.9°C (102°F); SpO₂, 97% on room air. Laboratory results show WBC 2.4 ×10³/mm³ (normal 3.2–9.8 ×10³/mm³), lactate 2.3 mmol/L, creatinine 0.8 mg/dL, and normal liver enzymes. Urinalysis reveals 5–10 WBC/hpf, trace leukocyte esterase, and no nitrites. Chest x-ray is clear. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Obtain peripheral blood cultures, begin IV broad-spectrum antibiotics, and consult for port removal"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Perform a lumbar puncture followed by broad-spectrum antibiotic therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Obtain paired blood cultures from the port and a peripheral vein and initiate broad-spectrum IV antibiotics"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Send urine culture and start IV ceftriaxone"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Start IV antibiotics and obtain echocardiography to evaluate for endocarditis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Although this approach appropriately includes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-section-id=\"cubaJv\" data-sememe-id=\"yOadEk\">empiric antibiotics</a> and source control, omitting cultures from the port limits diagnostic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zc8bd87864b8eaaa9403cde30b0f2b64c\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zc8bd87864b8eaaa9403cde30b0f2b64c\" data-section-id=\"vfWALk0\" data-sememe-id=\"zHarGN\">accuracy</a>. Paired <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a> from the device and a peripheral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Z6f8d5f3537f44c7bd7f1915d726b6360\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Z6f8d5f3537f44c7bd7f1915d726b6360\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">vein</a> are essential to confirm catheter-related infection through differential time-to-positivity.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>There is no evidence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">central nervous system</a> infection: no <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YL0nwg&anker=Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-learningcard-id=\"YL0nwg\" data-anker=\"Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-sememe-id=\"tK0XRS\">headache</a>, neck stiffness, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7704Mh&anker=Z5c6e37230ac0687b2722ec65d3bb632a\" data-learningcard-id=\"7704Mh\" data-anker=\"Z5c6e37230ac0687b2722ec65d3bb632a\" data-section-id=\"Zy1Zdj0\" data-sememe-id=\"R81lmi0\">altered mental status</a>. Pursuing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-l0DzT&anker=Z1e2677482998439ed77e51580e7a8efa\" data-learningcard-id=\"-l0DzT\" data-anker=\"Z1e2677482998439ed77e51580e7a8efa\" data-sememe-id=\"pn0L8g\">lumbar puncture</a> introduces unnecessary delay and procedural risk while failing to address the most probable infectious source.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Correct —  Even with a normal overlying <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> exam, intraluminal infection remains the most likely suspect of this unexplained <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> over her port site. Paired <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood cultures</a> provide diagnostic confirmation, and empiric IV <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> with early consideration for device removal are indicated.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Trace <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kg0mv2&anker=Z5a8141e3a6eead515951e305031e3722\" data-learningcard-id=\"kg0mv2\" data-anker=\"Z5a8141e3a6eead515951e305031e3722\" data-section-id=\"iJXJF_\" data-sememe-id=\"bg0HF2\">pyuria</a> without nitrites or urinary symptoms does not confirm a urinary source. In an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-section-id=\"h_XcL00\" data-sememe-id=\"P2YW3o\">immunocompromised</a> patient with an indwelling vascular device, attributing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> to a presumed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7i04Gf&anker=Zc27d78347d45b1423debf25ad883dd4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"7i04Gf\" data-anker=\"Zc27d78347d45b1423debf25ad883dd4c\" data-sememe-id=\"4ib37t\">UTI</a> risks missing a catheter-associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EH08Hh&anker=Zb7ed9a97a4df90768d08cfa474f89cc5\" data-learningcard-id=\"EH08Hh\" data-anker=\"Zb7ed9a97a4df90768d08cfa474f89cc5\" data-section-id=\"PaWWkP0\" data-sememe-id=\"ToW6Ym0\">bloodstream infection</a>. Hospital admission and broader evaluation are warranted.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-section-id=\"cubaJv\" data-sememe-id=\"yOadEk\">Empiric antibiotics</a> are reasonable in a hemodynamically stable, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">febrile</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-section-id=\"h_XcL00\" data-sememe-id=\"P2YW3o\">immunocompromised</a> patient, but further targeted evaluation, including appropriate cultures, should precede advanced imaging for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Zd1c6edf460701976c172357533193fca\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Zd1c6edf460701976c172357533193fca\" data-section-id=\"UYaboQ\" data-sememe-id=\"4KX3g_\">endocarditis</a>. This approach risks overlooking a more common and accessible infectious source.</div>",
